cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the creation of new images based on existing ones. The use of feature covariance matrices and the targeting of specific regions in the images also suggest that it could belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of evolutionary algorithms for artistic work suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The population-based evolutionary algorithm with mutation and crossover operators based on random walks suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of evolutionary algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
